We ordered 65.78  worth of food at 11:33 pm. Yes we understand that big orders take time. We knew this going in. Its 2:40 in the morning at the conclusion of this experience. However, Your stores representative that answered the phone throughout the order caused the entire experience to go downhill. We recieved half of the order and even that half was poorly cut and made wrong. Some people made compromises but others food was missing. We call and are told that the rest of order would arrive shortly. This would never occur. We were charged for delivery. The overall tax went up because of thag charge as well. We also didnt recieve our entire order. Now we reach the largest problem of all. Communication. The most essential part of the process. Reading is also important but if they didn't read the electronic order that SPECIFICALLY lists what the materials in the order should be comprised of to begin with we had to explore other routes. So after the first hour passes since the delivery of the first "half" of the order. We decide to call. We are told that we would have to wait an hour and half for the rest of the order or come in to return the wrong order in order to get my order. We're a 10 minute walk away. Your pizza tracker stated that the pizza was done. So how was half of the order missing/incorrect when you should have confirmed that everything was there. We call again to make sure that the food was coming. He rushes us off the phone 3 times. Hung up on us 3 times. We had to collectively head to the location with the pizza to get the pizza that was supposedly on its way. Every time we inquired he would speak over, cut us off or straight up hang up the phone.  When we did arrive we called him out on his behavior. No we were not nice but the fact remains is that I paid my money and didnt recieve what I was promised and that happens sometimes. But dont be rude and inconsiderate when you have my money. Its snakish behavior. We ask about the pizza that we were promised. The one that was supposedly on it way. He pulls the pizza out from behind the counter!All the rushing us off the phone and flat out disrespect to not not even have come through on your end of the bargain! I plan  to  follow up with the locations manager. I dont expect it to bear any fruits. But I wouldnt spend my first or last dollar here again. You cant get my order right and then you make it twice as hard to solve the issue. It motivates me to never come back. And if you dont want an experience like that dont spend your money here.
